 THE Federal Ministry of Petroleum Resources in conjunction with Department of Petroleum (DPR) will launch the National Gas Transportation Network Code next week Monday at the opening of the Nigeria International Petroleum Summit scheduled for Abuja. The Nigerian Gas Transportation Network Code is critical to government’s objective in firming up the country’s domestic gas obligation as well as promoting export. The network code will ensure that non-quality gas is pumped into the pipeline, guarantees gas pipeline integrity, open access to pipeline and common understanding on metering. “The review of the Network Code licensing framework and development of all its ancillary agreements have been firmed,” DPR said 